examples.en: Strange ideas existed in his mind.
The hostages existed on bread and water.
Hard feelings existed between the neighbours.
The game has existed in its present form for more than 300 years.
That such a report existed in Claudian's time cannot now be affirmed.
They evolved from simple life forms that existed millions of years ago.
Time and the weather have expunged any evidence that a thriving community once existed here.
Television commercials create appetency for products that the consumer may not have known even existed.
We can scarcely imagine what observers in some remote futurity will think of civilization as it existed at the dawn of the 21st century.
